programme.sub-title: The Girls Who Go Down Under

programme.title: America's Next Top Model: The Girl Who Picks a Fight
programme.desc: In this special recap episode, never-before-seen footage about the journey of the five remaining contestants is revealed, including a heated argument between two girls and a staged mock elimination by all the girls.
programme.sub-title: The Girl Who Picks a Fight

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: The finals - Royal Academy - first half!
programme.desc: The boys arrive at Royal Academy for the biggest game of their lives, but before they can begin they have to dispel the cloud of suspicion hanging over the place.
programme.sub-title: The finals - Royal Academy - first half!

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: The finals - Royal Academy - second half!
programme.desc: With Ray Dark safely shut away, the game against Royal has properly begin, and it’s a real game this time not a walkover. It’s neck and neck and back and forth and the air is full of penguins.
programme.sub-title: The finals - Royal Academy - second half!

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: The Legendary 11!
programme.desc: The boys still can't believe they beat Royal and are the new District Champion. After the celebratory dust settles, a mysterious figure walks into Seymour’s noodle bar.

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: This is it - the National tournament!
programme.desc: The Raimon 11 have set their sights on the National tournament and they’re determined to win it all.
programme.sub-title: This is it - the National tournament!

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: Soccer - ninja style!
programme.desc: With Nathan still on the team, for now, the Raimon 11 can move forward and concentrate on the Nationals.

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: Jude's decision!
programme.desc: The narrow victory over Shuriken has given Raimon confidence, but on the other side of the tournament there’s shock and awe at Royal’s complete destruction at the hands of Zeus Jr.

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: Break the unbreakable wall!
programme.desc: With their firepower boosted by the addition of Jude Sharp, the team are ready to tackle Farm Jr High and their unbreakable defence. But unless they get their passes coordinated then all their hard work will come to nothing!

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: The reincarnated genius!
programme.desc: Erik the Eagle is back! Like a phoenix he has risen from the ashes and come back to visit his old friend. Just in time too, Raimon Jr are desperate for some new moves, and the Tri Pegasus is just what they need. But can they perfect it in time?

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: The killer Triangle Z!
programme.desc: Raimon Jr are getting ready to play their next big opponent - Kirkwood Jr High, which just happens to be Axel Blaze’s old school.

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: The clash with Kirkwood Jr. High!
programme.desc: The Murdock brothers and their grudge are dominating Raimon Jr. at every turn, but they need to find the strength to overcome their malice if they’re going to make it to the final. If they don’t work together, their dream is finished!
programme.sub-title: The clash with Kirkwood Jr. High!

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: Go beyond the God Hand!
programme.desc: Raimon Jr. are through to the finals, but they’re all getting nervous about playing the terrifying Zeus Jr. Mark is convinced he’s not good enough, and if that weren’t enough to rattle nerves

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: A challenge from a God!
programme.desc: As the final against Zeus draws nearer, so does Raimon Jr’s anticipation and dread. The team are working hard, but the level they have to reach seems beyond their grasp. Will they get it together in time for the final?

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: Time for training camp!
programme.desc: The big game is almost on top of them but Mark still hasn’t mastered Majin the Hand. The coach decides to try and new tactic and everyone spends the night at school at a sleepover training camp.

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: The final battle!
programme.desc: This is it, the final of the Nationals has arrived. Zeus Jr. storm to an early lead and nothing Raimon Jr does has any effect on them. Are they really gods? Or is something else going on?

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: God vs Majin!
programme.desc: Raimon Jr. are down by three goals and are getting clobbered by the soccer gods of Zeus Jr. The situation looks completely hopeless and the clock is running down.

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: The Aliens Are Here!
programme.desc: The victory for the Raimon 11 proves to be very short lived, as only a few minutes after their win, the sky falls in. Literally! - All of a sudden the earth is overrun by aliens!

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: The Raimon 11 Fight Back!
programme.desc: The Raimon 11 have stepped up to try and save the world against the soccer players of Alius Academy, but it’s like pitting an ant against an elephant.

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: Take Down the Black 11!
programme.desc: The president has been kidnapped by aliens, and Mark and the others are determined to help him. The Inazuma Caravan travels to the park where he was kidnapped, ready to beat the aliens off.

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: The Alius Academy Threat
programme.desc: The tenacious Raimon 11 players never give up, and they’re going to try again against Alius Academy. But try as they might they can't even hold a candle to them.

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: The Search for the Legendary Striker!
programme.desc: The news that Axel is kicked off the team doesn’t go over well with most of the Raimon players, especially Kevin Dragonfly.
programme.sub-title: The Search for the Legendary Striker!

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: The Prince of Snow Land!
programme.desc: Raimon are excited and surprised when they finally meet Shawn Frost, but is he really as good as everyone says? There’s only one way to find out, and that’s to play a game against him.

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: Who is the New Ace Striker?
programme.desc: Shawn Frost is officially part of the Raimon 11, but there are still some teamwork kinks to iron out.
programme.sub-title: Who is the New Ace Striker?

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: The Alius Academy Attack!
programme.desc: Raimon have toughened up though their snowboard training and are ready to face Alius Academy one more time. But do they have what it takes to beat them?

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: Epsilon Attacks!
programme.desc: Just when everyone thought the earth had been saved, Alius Academy attack once more, but this time with Team Epsilon. These guys really mean business, and they’re beating up on a new school - Cloister Divinity in Kyoto.

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: The Hidden Power!
programme.desc: After the crushing defeat of Cloister Divinity, Raimon step up to fill the hole, with Scotty the substitute helping out on Celia’s urging. The results are strange and disheartening, but also encouraging in one way.

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: Royal Academy’s Comeback - Part 1!
programme.desc: Looks like Team Raimon have a new member, in the form of Sneaky Scotty. They’ll need all the help they can get though, because Ray Dark is back on the scene, in an unfeasibly silly submarine-based soccer stadium.

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: Royal Academy’s Comeback Part 2!
programme.desc: Raimon are smack in the middle of a game against Royal Academy Redux, and Ray Dark has convinced its players to use any and every means to win; even if it means the destruction of their minds and bodies.

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven: The Last Wyvern Blizzard!
programme.desc: The Inazuma Caravan finally comes home to recharge their batteries and…train a whole lot more. They find out that everybody’s been training to help them, including some old enemies!

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: Raimon's Football Club Is Rising From The Ashes!?
programme.desc: Determined to destroy Raimon, the Almighty Faith's School players will even risk crippling their opponents. The sight of this triggers an emotional change in Victor.
programme.sub-title: Raimon's Football Club Is Rising From The Ashes!?

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: J.P.'s Special Move!
programme.desc: The Raimon Eleven, all finally working together as a real team, defeat Almighty Faith School! But Fifth Sector strikes back, using Victor's sick brother to stop his rebellion and blackmail him into obeying once again.

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: A Reunion with Jude Sharp!
programme.desc: As Raimon prepares for its scheduled regional semifinal match with Ivy Selective College, they receive startling news: Raimon has been moved to another bracket in the tournament!

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: The Reunion Duel
programme.desc: After returning to the Satellite Sector, Yusei meets up with his old friend Crow and soon finds himself in a tag team Turbo Duel with Sector Security.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Dark Signs, Part 1
programme.desc: Yusei and Crow set off to confront the Dark Signers in an effort to stop them from destroying the Satellite Sector.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Dark Signs, Part 2
programme.desc: In an effort to save the Satellite Sector from being destroyed, Yusei agrees to face off against a former friend turned Dark Signer in a Shadow Duel.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Dark Signs, Part 3
programme.desc: With his life points on the line, Yusei confronts his former friend Kalin about their past in an effort to stop him from awakening the Army of Shadows.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Dark Signs, Part 4
programme.desc: The safety of the world hangs in the balance as Yusei tries to figure out a way to outduel and outmaneuver the unstoppable power of Kalin's dark deck.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Supersensory Shakedown
programme.desc: Leo is forced to take part in an extrasensory examination with the leader of the Arcadia Movement. Can Leo pass this pop quiz, or will this psychic showdown with Sayer leave Leo locked up forever?

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: The Dreaded Royal Academy!
programme.desc: The match begins, and Sam just barely manages to block a shot on goal -- Royal Academy is proving to be unlike any other team Raimon has faced.

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: Explosion Ultimate Thunder!
programme.desc: Raimon attempts a comeback using their super tactic, but end up surrendering a goal to Royal Academy instead. Raimon's offense is powerless in the face of Royal Academy's overwhelming special moves.

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: A Revolutionary Wind!
programme.desc: The day after their blistering battle in the regional semifinals, the Raimon players are ordered to meet at Royal Academy. There, they learn the stunning truth behind their match with the academy.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! ARC-V: The Pendulum Swings Both Ways: Part 1
programme.desc: Sylvio finally has just the thing to take Yuya down – a deck full of Pendulum Cards! Could Yuya's days in the spotlight be done for?
programme.sub-title: The Pendulum Swings Both Ways: Part 1

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! ARC-V: The Pendulum Swings Both Ways: Part 2
programme.desc: Yuya is off his game and on the run as Sylvio zeroes in on zeroing out his life points! If Yuya can’t get into the swing of things, this could be his final performance!
programme.sub-title: The Pendulum Swings Both Ways: Part 2

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! ARC-V: Making the Cut: Part 1
programme.desc: Sora is psyched to put on a showstopping duel for the fans, but his opponent Shay is set to turn Sora’s one man show into a no man show!

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! ARC-V: Making the Cut: Part 2
programme.desc: Sora and Shay's heated duel hits its boiling point when dark secrets about their hidden history come to light! Could there be something sinister behind Sora’s sweet-toothed smile?

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! ARC-V: Sora’s Secrets: Part 1
programme.desc: While Yuto is looking for answers, Sora is looking to get some revenge! But when these two tangle, Yuya finds out more than he ever expected!

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! ARC-V: Sora’s Secrets: Part 2
programme.desc: Surprises are in the cards as the battle between Sora and Yuto comes to an unexpected conclusion! But just when Yuya thinks he’s seen everything, a new face shows up on the scene that makes Yuya do a triple take!

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: Ravaging Fangs of the Sea Kings!
programme.desc: Determined to free Football from the clutches of Fifth Sector, the Raimon Eleven prepare to revolt. With the regional championship against Pirates Cove Merchant Marine Academy Academy coming up, morale is high, and losing is not an option.
programme.sub-title: Ravaging Fangs of the Sea Kings!

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: Fly Arion’s Fighting Spirit
programme.desc: The true revolution won't occur until the crowds watching are reminded of the power of real Football and decide to take a stand. The Raimon Eleven welcome back members who had quit, and the regional championship match begins.

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: The Autumn Sky Challengers!
programme.desc: The Holy Road tournament is finally underway. Surrounded by powerful enemies sent by Fifth Sector, the matches ahead will be the toughest yet. So the team practices harder than ever, reminding themselves that no opponent is unbeatable.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! GX: Doomsday Day, Part 2
programme.desc: Jaden continues his duel against the Shadow Rider known as Nightshroud, who has extra mysteries of his own!

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! GX: Field of Screams, Part 1
programme.desc: A vampiress named Camula is the second Shadow Rider to arrive at Duel Academy, but she's not there to suck blood, she's there to suck up souls!

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! GX: Field of Screams, Part 2
programme.desc: Camula continues to wreak havoc at Duel Academy, this time setting her sights on Zane.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! GX: Field of Screams, Part 3
programme.desc: Jaden steps up to confront Camula with the souls of Dr. Crowler and Zane at stake.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! GX: The Fear Factor
programme.desc: Jaden and the gang get sucked into a strange vortex where a duelist who bears a striking resemblance to Kaiba forces Jaden to face his worst fears or be overcome by them!

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! GX: Sibling Rivalry
programme.desc: Chazz's brothers have come back to Duel Academy for revenge, forcing Chazz to face them in a duel where if he loses, the deed to Duel Academy will be passed to them!

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: Gather, At The Flag Of Revolution
programme.desc: After seeing the newcomer's strange behavior in a practice match with the residents of ''Windsor Manor' flats, Bagriel Garcia (Gabi) begins to suspect the boy may be a Seed agent sent by Fifth Sector.
programme.sub-title: Gather, At The Flag Of Revolution

programme.title: Inazuma Eleven Go: The Fearsome Cyclone Arena
programme.desc: The first round of the Holy Road tournament gets underway at Aerodrome Arena. The Raimon Eleven are put on the defensive by Lunar Sea (Military) Academy's formations and attacks, which take full advantage of special contraptions unique to the venue.

programme.title: Casualty 24/7: Episode 7
programme.desc: Registrar Doctor Ashleigh Trimble takes the next call from paramedics. 81-year-old Roy is being blue lighted in, after falling over and landing badly on one of his artificial hips.

programme.title: Casualty 24/7: Episode 8
programme.desc: With an already busy department, Nurse Chloe Wesley answers the red emergency phone. A 23-month-old toddler is being rushed in with suspected sepsis, a life-threatening condition that attacks the internal organs.

programme.title: Casualty 24/7: Episode 9
programme.desc: Registrar Doctor Rob Cornford heads straight to Resus to treat 58-year-old window-fitter Craig who’s been blue-lighted in. He was working on a ladder on the first floor of a house when he fell and was knocked unconscious.

programme.title: Casualty 24/7: Episode 10
programme.desc: Sister Jane Hawksworth has clocked on for a night shift to find every bed in Barnsley Hospital is taken. To get the department moving again Sister Jane and the close-knit Casualty team will have to pull together.

programme.title: Casualty 24/7: Episode 11
programme.desc: Sister Benita Wainwright is leading the team, a day that she describes as “Chaos. There are people everywhere. It’s hard going. But staff pull together and make sure patients are looked after.”

programme.title: Casualty 24/7: Episode 12
programme.desc: At Barnsley Casualty the team clock on to a backlog of patients waiting to be transferred to wards. With no beds across the entire hospital, Sister Jane Hawksworth is battling to prevent patients being on trolleys for the NHS maximum of 12 hours.

programme.title: Casualty 24/7: Episode 13
programme.desc: After an extraordinarily busy few days, the team at Barnsley Casualty are struggling to clear the backlog of patients, and new arrivals are waiting up to 5 hours to see a doctor.

programme.title: Casualty 24/7: Episode 14
programme.desc: Sister Jane Hawksworth is on duty, ‘I think the sister team is strong, we are all strong women.' Sister Benita Wainwright heads to Resus where paramedics rush in a 14-year-old girl having a prolonged epileptic seizure.

programme.title: Casualty 24/7: Episode 15
programme.desc: It’s been a busy night at Barnsley Hospital’s Casualty Department, so the corridors are already packed full of patients when Sister Benita Wainwright arrives to head the shift.

programme.title: Casualty 24/7: Episode 16
programme.desc: In charge today at Barnsley Hospital’s Casualty Department is Consultant Doctor Julian Humphrey, ‘Emergency departments may look very chaotic but there’s a reasonable amount of structure. It’s organized chaos!’

programme.title: Casualty 24/7: Episode 17
programme.desc: Barnsley Casualty is facing one of its toughest shifts to date. With no children’s beds available across the whole of Yorkshire and a department filling up with poorly children the hospital is under pressure.

programme.title: Casualty 24/7: Episode 18
programme.desc: Registrar Doctor Gemma Hartshorne prepares to treat a man who has suddenly lost all feeling in his foot. Loss of blood flow is turning Roger's foot white - urgent treatment is needed to prevent amputation.

programme.title: Casualty 24/7: Episode 19
programme.desc: Trainee Advanced Nurse Practitioner Chantelle Proctor assesses a 49-year-old man rushed in by ambulance. Philip, who has a heart condition, collapsed at home and has been vomiting for the last ten days.

programme.title: Casualty 24/7: Episode 20
programme.desc: While people enjoy a most wonderful time of the year, Barnsley Hospital Casualty is open for business as usual, and the team are getting into the Christmas spirit. Consultant Doctor Julian Humphrey is leading the festive shift.

programme.title: Casualty 24/7: Episode 1
programme.desc: While Sister Jane runs outside to help a critical patient in the car park, Matron Val and Consultant Doctor Dave Walker need to negotiate with the Police who are stopping new arrivals entering the building.

programme.title: Dirty Home Rescue: Episode 9
programme.desc: Hayley Leitch and her cleaning team Tom Swire and Chesley Medley-Brown go to the rescue of Sue from Oxford whose house is overflowing with possessions. Sue married the love of her life in 2015, and he moved in, bringing everything he owned with him.

programme.title: Dirty Home Rescue: Episode 10
programme.desc: Hayley Leitch and her cleaning team Tom Swire and Chesley Medley-Brown go to the rescue of Linda and husband Andy from Bedau in South Wales whose house is overrun with animals and hasn’t been cleaned in 4 years.

programme.title: Dirty Home Rescue: Episode 11
programme.desc: Hayley Leitch and her cleaning team Tom Swire and Chesley Medley-Brown go to the rescue of Joanna from Birmingham, whose 2-bedroom flat is overflowing with possessions. Joanna works two jobs, leaving her no time to look after her home.

programme.title: Ekstreme samlere: Episode 1
programme.desc: Hoarding is on the rise and it's believed that 1 in 20 people could have a problem. With over 1.2 million problem hoarders in the UK today, one could be your neighbour?

programme.title: Ekstreme samlere: Episode 2
programme.desc: Susan's hoard has made her virtually homeless. Brian has dedicated his life to hoarding and his daughter is sick of it. Jake is lucky to be alive as his home almost burned to the ground in an inferno fuelled by the clutter he'd collected.

programme.title: Ekstreme samlere: Episode 3
programme.desc: Arthur's flat is packed with junk. Experts Caz and Tee are up for their toughest assignment ever. Khim is getting married but first she must clear her hoard. Mandi's passion for vintage clothes is out of control.

programme.title: Ekstreme samlere: Episode 4
programme.desc: Esther's hoard is so bad her landlord told her to clear up or clear out. Nigel receives a visit from fellow hoarder Janice.

programme.title: Ekstreme samlere: Episode 5
programme.desc: Paul's hoard fills his whole house, room after room after room is buried under 6 feet of clutter.

programme.title: Dirty Home Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: Hayley Leitch and her cleaning team Tom Swire and Chesley Medley-Brown go to the rescue of American born dog loving Dani from Shepton Mallet who moved to the UK with high hopes of living the English Country dream, but bad health got the better of her.

programme.title: Dirty Home Rescue: Episode 7
programme.desc: Hayley Leitch and her cleaning team Tom Swire and Chesley Medley-Brown go to the rescue of Eco warrior Karen from Somerset, who after many years of living off grid in a caravan, has struggled to adapt to living in, and looking after, a house.

programme.title: Dirty Home Rescue: Episode 8
programme.desc: Hayley Leitch and her cleaning team Tom Swire and Chesley Medley-Brown go to the rescue of Pippa and Matt from Oxford who have 6 kids all living in a 3-bedroom house. With both parents working full time, the house has taken a back seat for many years.

programme.title: Ekstreme samlere: Episode 1
programme.desc: In the picturesque city of Bath, Paul’s cottage is bursting at the seams with a lifetime’s collection of junk. Known locally as ‘boot cottage’ - because everything Paul owns and wears comes from car boot sales - every room is a no-go zone.

programme.title: Ekstreme samlere: Episode 2
programme.desc: In Harlow, 63-year-old Bubbles’ high-rise flat is packed with piles of junk she can’t bear to throw away. But it doesn’t end there she also has a staggering 4 lock ups stuffed to the gills with rubbish.

programme.title: Ekstreme samlere: Episode 3
programme.desc: In Mansfield Sue’s hoard is driving her family and grandchildren away and her husband Neil to distraction. Every room is crammed with clutter including a bedroom that looks more like a dolls graveyard than somewhere to sleep.

programme.title: Svenske krimsaker: Episode 702
programme.desc: Ekteparet Suzanne og Lars lever et stille og rolig liv på landet utenfor Stockholm. Men når Suzanne avlyser en viktig tenniskamp på kort varsel, blir hennes tennispartner mistenksom og varsler politiet.

programme.title: Svenske krimsaker: Episode 703
programme.desc: 18 år gamle Ndella Jack har nettopp kommet hjem fra bryllupsreise med mannen sin. Det som skulle være starten på deres liv sammen, får i stedet en brå slutt, da de blir ofre for et brutalt angrep.

programme.title: Svenske krimsaker: Episode 704
programme.desc: En sommernatt i Värmland bryter det ut slagsmål, hvoretter 21 år gamle Harout mottar et dødelig knivstikk. Politiet får mistanker om at et sjalusidrama kan være nøkkelen til å finne den skyldige.

programme.title: Svenske krimsaker: Episode 705
programme.desc: Psykolog Helena Bering forsvinner sporløst midt på dagen den 18. august 2004. Hun har nettopp avsluttet et møte med en klient på klinikken i Stockholm, når alle spor etter henne forsvinner.

programme.title: Svenske krimsaker: Episode 706
programme.desc: I mai 2017 ble småbarnsfaren Filip Viking funnet skutt i Katrineholm. Vitner skynder seg bort til ham og i forbindelse med forsøkene på å redde Filips liv, klarer de å se en lang svartkledd mann løpe fra åstedet.

programme.title: Norske Krimsaker: Episode 403
programme.desc: Marit Ødegaard jobber på en veikro ikke langt fra svenskegrensen. En oktoberdag i 2000 dukker hun ikke opp på jobb. Kort tid etter blir Marit funnet drept i hjemmet sitt

programme.title: Norske Krimsaker: Episode 404
programme.desc: I desember 2015 gjør gallerist Reidar Osen et ærend med varebilen sin da han blir kapret av ukjente gjerningsmenn, som truer ham på livet og krever to millioner kroner. Hvem står bak kidnappingen?

programme.title: Norske Krimsaker: Episode 405
programme.desc: To reindriftsutøvere fra Vest Finnmark havner i politiets søkelys etter å ha innrapportert flere hundre rovdyrskadde reinsdyr. Kan det virkelig være slik at de to har mishandlet dyrene sine for å motta erstatning?

programme.title: Svenske krimsaker: Episode 504

programme.title: Svenske krimsaker: Episode 505

programme.title: Svenske krimsaker: Episode 506

programme.title: Svenske krimsaker: Episode 507
programme.desc: 25 år gamle Anna blir funnet brutalt myrdet i sin nye leilighet i Karlstad. Når politiet etterforsker drapet, tyder alt på at gjerningsmannen kan være en person hun har møtt tidligere.

programme.title: Svenske krimsaker: Episode 601

programme.title: Svenske krimsaker: Episode 602
programme.desc: En regnfull morgen den 19. oktober 2004 dreper en ukjent mann en åtte år gammel gutt og en 56 år gammel kvinne i Linköping. Gjerningsmannen forsvinner sporløst og politiet må nå finne ut hvem han er.

programme.title: Svenske krimsaker: Episode 603
programme.desc: Politiet har ikke gitt opp å oppklare dobbeltdrapet i Linköping. Etter en endring i svensk lov i 2019, har politiet nå muligheten til å bruke kommersielle slektsdatabaser for å finne gjerningsmannen.

programme.title: Hundehviskeren: Hyde & Vada and Nacho
programme.desc: Hyde and Vada, both wolf hybrids have aggression issues to work out especially when it comes to other dogs. Nacho, bit a child, and shows aggression when he has his toy.

programme.title: Hundehviskeren: Charlotte, Elvis and Jack

programme.title: Hundehviskeren: Cesar and the Horse Whisperer (Chloe & Hobo, Ali)

programme.sub-title: Cesar and the Horse Whisperer (Chloe & Hobo, Ali)

programme.title: Hundehviskeren: Inside Puppy Mills

programme.title: Hundehviskeren: Nuna & Kane
programme.desc: NuNu the Chihuahua, fiercely attacks anyone who comes near his owner Tina. NuNu’s total opposite, Kane the Great Dane, is vehemently afraid of shiny surfaces

programme.title: Hundehviskeren: Harry & Brooks

programme.title: Hundehviskeren: Emily
